  "text": "The binary search algorithm is used to coordinate the transmissions from multiple tags to one reader [CITATION_1] . In the binary search algorithm, all tags transmit synchronously. The binary search algorithm (BSA) divides the tags involved in the collision to two sets, and only allows one set to transmit in subsequent time. If the transmitting set still incurs collision, the algorithm splits the set again until collision does not occur. After all tags in the transmitting set have their ID information received successfully, the other set resumes to transmit.",
